<TITLE> 1 killed in AL clashes in Barisal </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Barisal,March 21(bdnews24.com)One person was killed and at least 20 were injured in a clash between two local Awami League groups at Patarhat, Mehendiganj, on Saturday, said police. Reaz Uddin Polash (24), a Chhatra League worker, died on the way to Barisal Sher-e -Bangla Medical College Hospital. Of the injured, seven were admitted to the hospital and seven to Mehendigang Upazila health complex. Barisal police superintendent Toufique Mahbub Chowdhury told bdnews24.com that the clash occurred between supporters of local AL leaders Sardar Maheb Hossain and Maj (retd) Nasir. Maheb Hossain held Nasir's supporters responsible for the incident, saying Polash was one of his supporters. But Nasir blamed Maheb's men for the killing. Maheb also alleged that Nasir's supporters harassed his men and tried to attack his house as a meeting was being held over the postponement of the Jan 22 Mehendiganj Upazila election. bdnews
